org.fhnw.aigs.commons.communication

Class JoinMessage

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.fhnw.aigs.commons.communication.Message
      • org.fhnw.aigs.commons.communication.JoinMessage

  • public class JoinMessage
extends Message
    This message is sent to the server when a player wants to join a message. Usually the "startGame" method triggers this message.

    v1.1 JoinType added

    • Field Detail

      • gameName

        private java.lang.String gameName
        The name of the game as a String, e.g. "TicTacToe"

      • joinTime

        private java.util.Date joinTime
        The time the player sent the join request to a game

      • gameMode

        private GameMode gameMode
        The game mode which can either be SinglePlayer, Multiplayer or Test. This attribute can be used to control the game's logic.

      • partyName

        private java.lang.String partyName
        If desired, a player can name the party he wants so play in. So he or she can make sure that he will start a game with those people who are also willing to join the game.

      • joinType

        private JoinType joinType
        The type of joining a game. The server will interprete this value and:
        a) join a random waiting game or create a new one (Auto)
        b) Create an new private game with the party name (CreateNewPrivateGame)
        c) Create an new public game with the party name (CreateNewGame)
        d) Join a particular game with the defined party name (JoinParticularGame)
        Since:
        v1.1

    • Constructor Detail

      • JoinMessage

        public JoinMessage()
        Empty constructor. This is needed for JAXB parsing.

      • JoinMessage

        public JoinMessage(java.lang.String gameName,
                   GameMode gameMode,
                   JoinType joinType)
        Constructor used to generate a JoinMessage without any preferences. This message will be interpreted by the server. The server will start a new game or join an existing game based on the JoinMessage.
        Parameters:
        gameName - Name of the game, e.g. TicTacToe
        gameMode - The GameMode. It can either be SinglePlayer,
        joinType - The JoinType MultiPlayer or Test.

      • JoinMessage

        public JoinMessage(java.lang.String gameName,
                   GameMode gameMode,
                   java.lang.String partyName,
                   JoinType joinType)
        Constructor used to generate a JoinMessage with a party preferences. This message will be interpreted by the server. The server will start a new game or join an existing game based on the JoinMessage. The player will only be joined with other players using the same partyName in their JoinMessages.
        Parameters:
        gameName - Name of the game, e.g. TicTacToe
        gameMode - The GameMode. It can either be SinglePlayer,
        partyName - The name of the party
        joinType - The JoinType MultiPlayer or Test.
